race.description: Kelly Memorial Sponsored By Kellys Agnvet Handicap
race.comment: THE DAILY PLANET (1) last appeared two weeks ago over 1400m at Hamilton when he finished third. This is his first run for the Aaron Purcell stable and there's plenty to like about his prospects down in grade from a good draw. HIGH DELTA (6) built on a nice second two starts back at St Arnaud with success as public elect over 1200m at Mildura two-and-a-half weeks ago, getting home by a long neck. Needs to be at his best to beat this field but he has the ability to mix it with them. LIBERTY RAE (14) ran a better race last start, finishing 2 lengths away in fourth over 1200m at Dunkeld. Better than recent efforts suggest and should be at peak fitness now. MUMMSIE (10) has been disappointing this prep, but most runs have been in higher grade than this so she might be ready to do something. HAATHER (4) should now be at peak fitness and while he has a poor winning strike-rate, the draw gives him the chance to sneak a Top 4 spot.
